article.headline: Boilermakers shoot 64% from floor
article.linkText: No. 11 Purdue puts the hurt on Wisconsin-Milwaukee
article.story:
WEST LAFAYETTE, Indiana (Ticker) -- Shereka Wright and Katie 
Gearlds both had 17 points to lead No. 11 Purdue over
Wisconsin-Milwaukee, 88-60.

Wright converted 7-of-13 field-goal attempts and blocked a pair
of shots.

Gearlds connected on a pair of 3-point baskets, pulled down five
rebounds and handed out four assists for the Boilermakers
(2-1), who put together both a 15-3 and 11-4 run in the first
half to take charge.

Erin Lawless netted 11 points and Erika Valek added eight and
six assists for Purdue, which shot 64.3 for the game, the
fifth-best percentage in school history.

Maria Viall led the Panthers with 23 points and 12 rebounds. The
senior center moved into fourth place on Wisconsin-Milwaukee's
all-time scoring list with 1,403 points.

Freshman Kiley Johnson added 13 points and six rebounds for the
Panthers (1-2), who committed 26 turnovers in the loss.
